caption.text:
Analysis and comparison of proteins via different techniques.
The first three columns contain the sample and the theoretical weight of the monomer and hexamer. For SEC, and AUC the elution volume and sedimentation coefficient were converged to molecular weight. The DLS values are based on the main peak from SEC, except for Pizza-PH, which used the monodisperse fraction with the correct estimated molecular weight. AUC and ESI only show the values of the main peak.
